html:
https://www.paywithisis.com/terms.html
"(d) Updates. We may from time to time provide updates to the Isis Wallet on your Isis-Enabled Mobile Device. These updates may be provided automatically “over the air” and are designed to improve, enhance and further develop the Isis Wallet. These updates may take the form of revisions to the Terms of Service and/or Privacy Policy, and can include Electronic Communications (see Section 7 below), bug fixes, enhanced functions and new software modules. You agree to receive and install such updates (and permit us to deliver these to you) as part of your use of the Isis Wallet, and understand that fees and charges may apply (see Section 4 below)."

It's pretty standard to do this but it's still not ideal.

--
